CHAPTER XXXI.

· The Consul Cn. Servilius Geminus sets sail (from Ostia, see Chapter XI.)

with a fleet of one hundred and twenty ships. Takes hostages from the corsicana and Sardinians. Lays waste the island of Meninx. Receives ten talents of silver to spare the island of Cercina.
